  "body": "How to verify if my contract constructor has array params?\r\n\r\nLet say i have a contract that have constructor accepting 2 params, string and array\r\n\r\n````\r\nconstructor(string memory param1, address[] memory param2) public {\r\n}\r\n````\r\n\r\nI want to verify it using etherscan verify plugin. \r\n\r\nTried code below it doesn't work.\r\n````\r\nconst bre = require(\"@nomiclabs/buidler\");\r\nawait bre.run('verify', {\r\n        address: '0xXXXXXX,\r\n        constructorArguments: ['Some params', ['test']],\r\n    });\r\n````\r\nThis will result in error `Invalid value  for argument constructorArguments of type string`.\r\n",
